| Command (macOS / Linux) | Example | What you see / learn | Windows PowerShell Command | Example | What you see / learn |
|-------------------------|---------|----------------------|----------------------------|---------|----------------------|
| `whois`                 | `whois reuters.com` | Domain registrar, creation date, contact info (if public) | `whois` *(may need `nslookup` if not installed)* | `whois reuters.com` | Domain registrar, creation date |
| `ping`                  | `ping reuters.com`  | Checks if the site is online; shows latency and IP address  | `ping` | `ping reuters.com` | Site availability, IP, latency |
| `nslookup`              | `nslookup reuters.com` | DNS info; find IPs and DNS servers | `nslookup` | `nslookup reuters.com` | DNS info; IP addresses of servers |
| `dig`                   | `dig reuters.com`   | Detailed DNS records (A, MX, TXT, etc.) | — | — | — |
| `traceroute`            | `traceroute reuters.com` | Path of packets from your computer to the server | `tracert` | `tracert reuters.com` | Packet route to server |
| `curl`                  | `curl -I https://reuters.com` | Fetch HTTP headers; see server type, security headers | `curl` *(Windows 10+)* | `curl -I https://reuters.com` | HTTP headers |
| `host`                  | `host reuters.com`  | Quick check of IP addresses and DNS info | `systeminfo` | `systeminfo` | Info about your local system (good context for students) |
